post.description:
Validates an MSO MDoc DeviceResponse.

  1. Verifies the provided value is a DeviceResponse encoded using Base64 URL-Safe encoding
  2. For each contained Document verifies:
    1. It contains non-expired ValidityInfo
    2. It is of the expected document type
    3. It contains IssuerSigned items with valid Digests
    4. It is signed by a trusted Issuer (checked against a configured X5C chain)

requestBody.description: The value to validate as an MSO Mdoc Device Response encoded using Base64 URL safe encoding.

post.description:
Validates an SD-JWT Verifiable Credentials.

Verifies the provided value:

  1. Is an SD-JWT-VC serialized using compact serialization
  2. Is signed by a trusted Issuer (checked against a configured X5C chain)
  3. Contains a valid KeyBinding JWT (with this Verifier as the Audience and the provided Nonce value)

requestBody.description: The value to validate as an SD-JWT Verifiable Credential and the expected Nonce of the KeyBinding JWT.
